title: For Sale/Trade:  French Model 1816/1822 Calvary Pistol
location: North Raleigh, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
It started out as flintlock, probably closer to the 1822 date than the 1816 date. It is an original French Model 1822 Cavalry Pistol or "Pistolet d'Arçon Modèle 1822 T Bis". These were converted from the Model 1816 Flintlock Cavalry Pistol and converted to percussion at various times beginning circa 1822. My pistol is an early one dated 1816. Smooth bore with ramrod. The stock and barrel are stamped with various French marks, and have what appears to be the original serial number 410; barrel tang is stamped, "Mle 1816 bis". Lockplate indicates manufacture at "Mutzig" arsenal as so stamped. Believed to be ~.70 caliber (~17.7mm).

All the mechanics work, but I have not fired it, and I don't recommend it. I will accept cash or ammo.
